<br>
You are really oversimplifying this to the point of making yourself sound ill informed.<br>
<br>
I don't care that enchanters can kill Trak with charmed frogs or Juggs. The old world is dead.<br>
<br>
I care that 1 chanter, 1 druid, 1 cleric were able to take down a named mob in PoS that hits for 1200 damage and wiped 10 people who tried him moments before.<br>
<br>
If you truly believe that encounter was designed for 3 people, you are a fool. PoP has been glaringly obvious as designed for guilds or large groups. The raid feature was no coincedence. Don't sit here and spout off BS that this does not trivialize those encounters. I don't know anyone in the game who can parse out 400DPS, except for charmers. The risk is not there. So don't try and justify that. People can parse out 400DPS without hasting the pet. Runes and good cleric heals will keep a mob that has broken charm from eating the chanter long enough to recharm it.<br>
<br>
Second, if you believe that a mob that has been charmed 3 times can not be recharmed, again, you are a fool. I have seen the same druid use a charmed frog for 4 or 5 HOURS in PoS to kill other mobs farming AA. Don't presume to tell me he only charmed it 3 times. He intentionally breaks charm after every fight to reapply snare and recharm it. Sometimes he will even break charm to let the mob heal itself as an NPC.<br>
<br>
Third, you state 1 mage can outdamage 3 necros. This is true, and a natural thing because of the way necros work as opposed to mages. It is also true that 1 necro can survive a fight and win (Via Fear/Root/FD/Harmshield) where 3 mages would be hard pressed to do the same.  Accept your strong points as a class. You aren't a nuclear bomb, you are a poisoned needle. You subtley are able to do a lot of damage and win a fight, while we stand there chucking pets and nukes hoping to whatever power there is that the mob dies before we run out of mana.  When our pet dies, we run for holy hell. When your DoTs wear off, you lie there face to the dirt chuckling as the sound of dying mages surrounds you.<br>
<br>
Lastly, if you believe I can outdamage a charmed frog, you are a fool. Sure, I can do a lot of damage. I can chain nuke with FoT and maybe come to a third of the damage of the frog, till the giant gets bored with me and summons me over, flattening me like a penny on a train track. 3 Mages could not outdamage a Chanter in BoT who uses a charmed giant to kill 65 bosses. <br>
<br>
Your defense, at this point, lacks any credibility or hard data.  Now, this is not to say I think you aren't wise. I have read your comments here for ages, but I feel your attempt to defend this is blinding you to things you know.  <br>
<br>
Tarqal<br>
