<br>
Any more than 2 enchanters on a raid is redundant and is boring. Crowd control is useless in many of the high end game encounters such as Veeshan's Peak and Temple of Veeshan. Heck, even wimpy places like Skyfire, CC is useless. And when you do go into a zone that allows you do to what you were made to do, if there is one or two more enchanters there, you're fighting over who gets to mez what. (Usually playfully so... but still, it's pretty ridiculous how enchanters do NOT stack with each other well...)<br>
<br>
Unless... they charm. Charming is what sets them apart. When I heard about CoD I thought to myself, &quot;Finally! Something cool I can do!&quot; Then my next thought was &quot;wait, people will whine and say we should be nerfed then soon it will be.&quot; and that's exactly what's happening. I am sure you will get your way and it will be nerfed and us enchanters can go back to twiddling our thumbs or playing alts. I'll be sure to thank you guys when that happens.<br>
<br>
You guys who are so worried about us outdamaging you or other classes with our mean ole charm. Take it away you say. You all do realize that we have NO damage outside charming, right? My best nuke at level 62 is worse than a druid's 55th level nuke and I don't get an upgrade till level 64. I suppose you'll say &quot;go back to crowd controlling, that's what you're good at&quot; .... and I hope when you do, you petition Sony and ask them to give us a bit more zones in the higher end game where CC is actually worth it. I really don't like having to sit and watch wizards rooting adds with their super root or tanks tanking adds when would've liked to mez. But CC is too unreliable in the higher end game. <br>
<br>
For you to sit here and say charming comes without risk, well, I think YOU are the fool. And FYI: Gojirax did NOT say that you can't charm a mob more than three times. What he said was that it becomes more RESISTANT after three times. I noticed this at a very early age and stopped charming for a long time because of it. I've asked around and talked to a few different charming classes (druid/necro) and they agree that once you've charmed a mob three times, it's time to get rid of it because it doesn't seem to hold as well.<br>
<br>
