<br>
I haven't see any argument to how it's balanced except for death, which really isn't a big deal anymore.<br>
<br>
Mages normal pets shouldn't be outdamaging a charmed pet, I agree with that. But the power jump is way way way to high.<br>
<br>
The chanter pet has an immensely larger pool of hitpoints and the DPS is off the charts compared to mage pets (and not as situational, like backstabber pet).<br>
<br>
The idea that slowing and mezzing isnt a necessary thing is ludicrous. Slow probably saw the second largest upgraded in power (next to charm) with pop. A group doesn't do anything decent without it. Haste and KEI without having to hit the nexus is also very big in keeping pick up groups together, so lets not take that out of the equation as well. Also add on the free dire charm pets (lets face it they handed them out this time with the low level mobs they put in the pop zones) chanters get DPS comparable to mages pet.<br>
<br>
If you have issue with enchanters being bored in groups find a way to fix that without blurring the already screwy lines. Unless we have gotten to the point where DPS is the only balance in the game?<br>
<br>
Oh and lastly.<br>
<br>
&quot;Charm isn't going to make anyone obsolete.&quot;<br>
